nry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Maud Bockerel was born about 1358, in Devonport, Devon, England, United Kingdom, her father, Henry Bockerel II, was 30 and her mother, F Bockerel, was 25. She married Walter Dennis in 1375, in Devon, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 4 sons. She died in 1390, in Devon, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 33."},"et":{"Abt 1358–1390":"umbes 1358–1390","1358–1390":"1358–1390","1346–Male":"1346–Surnud","1380–1414":"1380–1414","1372–1392":"1372–1392","1380–Male":"1380–Surnud","1382–Male":"1382–Surnud","1390–Male":"1390–Surnud","1330–Male":"1330–Surnud","1335–Female":"1335–Surnud","about 1382":"umbes 1382","1330":"1330","Abt 1358":"umbes 1358","1372":"1372","1382":"1382","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1390":"1390","       1357":"1357","1414":"1414","1358":"1358","1335":"1335","1346":"1346","1375":"1375","Devonport, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devonport, Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devonshire, England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dyrham, Gloucestershire, England":"Dyrham, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Of Allertrewe,Devon,England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Giddecote, Devonshire, England, United Kingdom":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Devon, England":"Devon, England","Giddecote,Devonshire,England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1358–1390":"noin 1358–1390","1358–1390":"1358–1390","1346–Male":"1346–Kuollut","1380–1414":"13